  "body": "Hi guys,\r\nthis issue is for release planning around the Berlin HF. I would like to do at most two releases here, one final `v7.0.0` release finishing up on [v7.0.0-beta.1](https://github.com/ethereum/tests/releases/tag/v7.0.0-beta.1) and providing some stable ground to update the test runners to on a pre-Berlin state.\r\n\r\nWe have re-started to run the tests from the current `develop` state against EthereumJS VM, see https://github.com/ethereumjs/ethereumjs-vm/pull/743. We are running into some issues there (some `BlockChain` tests are failing), I would use the occasion to work on some `v7.0.0` release notes along our work there and open here as a PR so that others can profit.\r\n\r\nI would then prepare one or more `v8.0.0-beta.x` releases for Berlin-integrating releases once first PRs are merged here.\r\n\r\n@winsvega how do you plan to proceed with the [LegacyTests](https://github.com/ethereum/tests/blob/develop/LegacyTests/) folder separation. Will there be a dedicated switch with a move of the `Istanbul` tests over there at some PIT? Or will the `Berlin` tests reside in the main test folders for now?\r\n\r\n",
